<h2>What it is all about?</h2>
<p> Every players controls <em>three shapes</em> (randomly chosen from circle, star, pentagon, square, triangle and crescent). Every one of them eats two other shapes (pictured near the bottom of every shape). If player's shape <em>eats</em> other shape, the player <em>gains two points</em>. But if player's shape <em>is eaten</em>, the player <em>loses one point</em>. Every eaten shape is replaced by a new one, randomly chosen and placed on a random position on board.</p>

<img src="cheatSheet128.png" alt="Who eats who"/>
<p>The player can steer <em>one shape at a time</em>. The shape can be ordered to perform successively some actions, however once the order has been given, it cannot be cancelled. By <em>switching</em> active shape it is possible to control all of ones shapes.</p>
<img src="teleports.png" alt="Teleports kinds"/>
<p>By using a <em>teleport</em> it is possible to rapidly move a shape to different position on board. Every teleport can be used by only <em>one kind of shapes</em>. Using <em>items</em> gives player big advantage, even if only for a little while. It is possible for a shape to have many active items at a time. Below are descriptions of effects of using various items:</p>
